A man was killed and his wife seriously injured on Friday when lightning struck them in Magombani Village, Matuga, Kwale County. The two were sheltering under a tree at 5pm as it was raining heavily. HEAVY RAIN County Commissioner Karuku Ngumo said the woman was taken to Kwale Hospital for treatment in a critical condition. "They were coming from their shamba when the incident occurred," he said. The heavy rains pounding most parts of the country in the past few days has left a trail of destruction and suffering. On March 2, a woman and her two children were killed when they were struck by lightning in Kamujwa Village, Tharaka Nithi County.  